The paper discusses the use of formal methods for the specification, simulation, development, and verification of distributed interactive systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also mentions the limitations of two-valued logic and the need to use fuzzy logic, which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also extends a model-based method, which could fall under the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. The paper also discusses the specification of components, which could fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. Finally, the paper deals with interactive systems, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
